Each week, students explore apocalyptic themes such as nuclear war, zombies, viruses and germs, and global warming.
This semester, when religion professor Stuart Charmé decided to teach a course on the end of the world, he knew he had an irresistible glimpse: The end of the Mayan “long regressive account” on December 21, to which many people have clinged as proof that the end of the world is coming.
