But he pointed out that there is apocalyptic anxiety in Western culture, dating back several centuries, in which people react to the changes around them by predicting the end of the world.
The Internet has caused a rise in these speculations.
“In other places people don’t think about this,” he said.
Mostly in the English-speaking world.
